# Slivki agent crew

This project has specialized Cursor subagents in `.cursor/agents/`. Delegate with
the Task tool / subagent invoke when the job matches. Do not reinvent roles.

## Default routing

| Work | Agent |
| --- | --- |
| SwiftUI screens, stores, decoding, Simulator fixes | `swift-expert` |
| Multi-screen shopping feature / navigation + API | `mobile-app-developer` |
| Small reproduced UI mismatch vs site screenshot | `ui-fixer` |
| Layout/IA decision before big UI change | `ui-designer` |
| Prod PHP / mobile API templates on server | `php-pro` |
| New/changed API contract (cart/auth/orders/slug) | `api-designer` |
| Failing test/build, crash, wrong runtime behavior | `debugger` |
| Capture mobile-site evidence / DOM parity | `browser-debugger` |
| After substantive diff: correctness review | `reviewer` |
| Acceptance / release QA checklist | `qa-expert` |
| Prod deploy / TestFlight rollout safety | `deployment-engineer` |
| Auth/Keychain/secrets/SSH security check | `security-auditor` |

## Working rules

- Active goal: native SwiftUI parity with `https://slivki-shop.ru` mobile site.
- Evidence first for UI: `Docs/Design/screenshots/` or live site capture.
- Keep `swift test` and Xcode `Slivki` scheme green before calling a flow done.
- Prefer smallest safe patch. No broad rewrite unless asked.
- Never print private SSH keys. Use `ssh slivki-prod` / `ssh slivki-prod-admin`.
- After non-trivial iOS or API change, run `reviewer` before finishing.
- For UI parity passes, prefer `browser-debugger` → `ui-fixer` / `swift-expert`.

## SSH / prod

- Hosts configured locally: `slivki-prod`, `slivki-prod-admin`
- Site root: `/var/www/www-root/data/www/slivki-shop.ru`
- Safe prod edit: patch locally → `/tmp` → `php -l` → backup → install
